edu.berkeley.cs.jqf.fuzz.guidance

Class ReproGuidance

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.berkeley.cs.jqf.fuzz.guidance.ReproGuidance
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Guidance

    public class ReproGuidance
extends Object
implements Guidance
    A front-end that provides a specified set of inputs for test case reproduction, This class enables reproduction of a test case with an input file generated by a guided fuzzing front-end such as AFL.
    Author:
    Rohan Padhye

      • generateCallBack

        public Consumer<TraceEvent> generateCallBack(Thread thread)
        Returns a callback that can log trace events to a trace file.

        If traceDir was non-null during the construction of this Guidance instance, then one log file per thread of execution is created in this directory. The callbacks generated by this method write trace event descriptions in sequence to their own thread's log files.

        Specified by:
        generateCallBack in interface Guidance
        Parameters:
        thread - the thread whose events to handle
        Returns:
        callback that can log trace events to a trace file
